
Basic instructions to get started with Sarus follow below. Please refer to the Sarus
documentation for more information on how to install, configure and use Sarus.

1. Extract this archive in the installation directory.

   cd /opt/sarus
   sudo tar xf sarus.tar.gz

2. Run the configuration script to finalize the installation of Sarus.

    cd /opt/sarus/1.0.0-rc8 # adapt folder name to actual version of Sarus
    sudo ./configure_installation.sh

3. Use Sarus, e.g.:

    export PATH=/opt/sarus/1.0.0-rc8/bin:$PATH
    sarus images
    sarus run alpine cat /etc/os-release
